<author><name><![CDATA[Lloyd Gordon]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-04-24T19:13:59-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-04-24T19:13:59-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12210#p12210</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12210#p12210"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Soldering]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12210#p12210"><![CDATA[
Wire wrap wire is a fairly small guage wire that comes on a spool, single conductor, insulated and the perfect size wire for NES carts. It comes in different colours which is convenient. You can buy a wire wrap tool which makes it really easy to use. It's pretty cheap as is the wrapping tool. Both Amazon and RadioShack have cheap desoldering irons around $10-$13 USD. I don't know if they deliver to Brazil or for how much.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=236">Lloyd Gordon</a> — Mon Apr 24, 2006 7:13 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
