<author><name><![CDATA[Lloyd Gordon]]></name></author>
<updated>2006-04-24T12:30:07-07:00</updated>
<published>2006-04-24T12:30:07-07:00</published>
<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12189#p12189</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12189#p12189"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Rewiring TLROM cart for use with W27E512]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=1397&amp;p=12189#p12189"><![CDATA[
Don't get upset. The boards are really hard to completely destroy. I've ripped out traces, cracked resistors and all sorts of other stuff. Just take your time and bypass the areas with some wire-wrap wire, which is what I use on the cartridges. I've even taken out mapper chips and wired them to other boards and just left the PCB portion hanging loose in the plastic cartridge and it works fine. Don't throw out your "wrecked" cart.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=236">Lloyd Gordon</a> — Mon Apr 24, 2006 12:30 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
